TITLE: Defining Sign/Skip Match Condition (CMBC-SIGN-SKIP-MATCH.1)
DESCRIPTION: Defines the 'sign-skip-match(a,b,c,t)' property. It asserts that if a block 'a' is sequentially rooted ('sequ-rooted(a)') and two blocks 'b' and 'c' of the same height can both be verified from 'a' via skip-tracing ('skip-trace(a,b,t)' and 'skip-trace(a,c,t)'), then their headers must be identical ('b.Header = c.Header'). If this property evaluates to false, it indicates conflicting headers and thus an attack.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cometbft/cometbft/blob/main/spec/light-client/detection/detection_003_reviewed.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
[CMBC-SIGN-SKIP-MATCH.1]

Let *a*, *b*, *c*, be light blocks and *t* a time, we define
*sign-skip-match(a,b,c,t) = true* iff the following implication
evaluates to true:

- *sequ-rooted(a)* and
- *b.Header.Height = c.Header.Height* and
- *skip-trace(a,b,t)*
- *skip-trace(a,c,t)*

implies *b.Header = c.Header*.
```

