TITLE: Transaction Addition and Deduplication in Mempool - Bluespec
DESCRIPTION: Defines actions for adding transactions to a node's mempool, distinguishing between first-time and duplicate transactions based on cache state. These actions update both the mempool structure and the sender tracking, respecting validity checks and ensuring no redundant addition of senders. Optional sender logic allows differentiation between user and peer sources.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cometbft/cometbft/blob/main/spec/mempool/gossip/flood.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: bluespec
CODE:
```
action tryAddTx(node, _incomingMsgs, optionalSender, tx) = 
    if (not(hash(tx).in(node.Cache())))
        node.tryAddFirstTimeTx(_incomingMsgs, optionalSender, tx)
    else
        node.processDuplicateTx(_incomingMsgs, optionalSender, tx)
```

LANGUAGE: bluespec
CODE:
```
action tryAddFirstTimeTx(node, _incomingMsgs, optionalSender, tx) = all {
    mempool' = mempool.update(node, st => {
        cache: st.cache.join(hash(tx)),
        txs: if (valid(tx)) st.txs.append(tx) else st.txs,
        ...st }),
    senders' = senders.update(node, ss =>
        if (valid(tx)) ss.addSender(tx, optionalSender) else ss),
    incomingMsgs' = _incomingMsgs,
    peers' = peers,
}
```

LANGUAGE: bluespec
CODE:
```
action processDuplicateTx(node, _incomingMsgs, optionalSender, tx) = all {
    senders' = senders.update(node, ss =>
        if (node.Txs().includes(tx)) ss.addSender(tx, optionalSender) else ss),
    mempool' = mempool,
    incomingMsgs' = _incomingMsgs,
    peers' = peers,
}
```

