TITLE: Channel Handling in Publisher in Go
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how the publisher treats buffered and unbuffered channels differently. It blocks on unbuffered channels and uses non-blocking sends on buffered channels, terminating slow subscriptions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cometbft/cometbft/blob/main/docs/references/architecture/tendermint-core/adr-033-pubsub.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
for each subscription {
    out := subscription.outChan
    if cap(out) == 0 {
        // block on unbuffered channel
        out <- msg
    } else {
        // don't block on buffered channels
        select {
            case out <- msg:
            default:
                // set the error, notify on the cancel chan
                subscription.err = fmt.Errorf("client is too slow for msg)
                close(subscription.cancelChan)

                // ... unsubscribe and close out
        }
    }
}
```

