TITLE: Message Delay Parameter
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the MSGDELAY parameter that bounds the maximum end-to-end delay for proposal message delivery between correct processes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cometbft/cometbft/blob/main/spec/consensus/proposer-based-timestamp/pbts-sysmodel.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
**[PBTS-MSG-DELAY.0]**

There exists a system parameter `MSGDELAY` for end-to-end delays of proposal messages,
such for any two correct processes `p` and `q`:

- If `p` sends a proposal message `m` at real time `t` and `q` receives `m` at
  real time `t'`, then `t <= t' <= t + MSGDELAY`.
```

