TITLE: Clock Precision Specification
DESCRIPTION: Defines the PRECISION parameter that bounds the maximum difference between synchronized process clocks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cometbft/cometbft/blob/main/spec/consensus/proposer-based-timestamp/pbts-sysmodel.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
**[PBTS-CLOCK-PRECISION.0]**

There exists a system parameter `PRECISION`, such that
for any two processes `p` and `q`, with local clocks `C_p` and `C_q`:

- If `p` and `q` are equipped with synchronized clocks,
 then for any real-time `t` we have `|C_p(t) - C_q(t)| <= PRECISION`.
```

