TITLE: Deterministic Byte Reordering Algorithm
DESCRIPTION: Detailed steps for transforming serialized Protocol Buffer messages into a canonical representation by applying specific ordering and filtering rules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cometbft/cometbft/blob/main/docs/references/rfc/tendermint-core/rfc-007-deterministic-proto-bytes.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
1. Does not add any of the data from unknown fields into the type to hash.
2. Reordered all message fields to be in tag-sorted order.
3. Reordered the contents of all `repeated` fields to be in lexicographically sorted order.
4. Deleted all default values from the byte representation.
5. Recursively performed these operations on any length-delimited subfields.
```

